<p t="698320" d="4320">Madrid is a funny city because there&#39;s 
a lot of little details that you can  </p>
<p t="702640" d="5520">find on top of the doors, on top of the 
buildings—you know, there&#39;s certain things.  </p>
<p t="708160" d="5920">You really have to look up for those kind 
of details that make this city special.</p>
<p t="714080" d="4240">For example, over on Gran Vía—Madrid’s 
central hub for shopping and Broadway  </p>
<p t="718320" d="4400">shows—you’ll find some pretty crazy details 
if you just look up. Like this statue of a  </p>
<p t="722720" d="4480">Roman goddess shooting down a phoenix on the 
other side of the street. And if you look down,  </p>
<p t="727200" d="3600">the pavement below actually 
has a print of the arrows, too.</p>
<p t="730800" d="3680">It&#39;s fun stuff like this that made me 
love this place whenever I first visited.</p>
<p t="734480" d="3120">And speaking of fun, I know 
a neighborhood for that.</p>
<p t="737600" d="4800">We decided to move over to La Chueca. 
This is a neighborhood you want to party.</p>
<p t="742400" d="5920">Let me tell you that we are not very 
party people. At least not anymore.  </p>
<p t="748960" d="18320">So we are here just exploring 
and finding a place to eat.</p>
<p t="767280" d="5280">I remember when I came here with my family a 
lot of years ago, this neighborhood—it looked  </p>
<p t="772560" d="4800">so different. It had a lot of personality 
and definitely it changed through the years.</p>
<p t="777360" d="4480">Yeah. Unfortunately, you know, I think 
this neighborhood is for someone—it  </p>
<p t="781840" d="3920">just maybe isn&#39;t for us anymore. And that 
could be largely due to the fact that we  </p>
<p t="785760" d="4160">have traveled to a lot of neighborhoods like 
this recently through our travels. You know,  </p>
<p t="789920" d="5600">the gentrified neighborhood of the city. There&#39;s 
lots of coffee shops here and lots of cute bars.  </p>
<p t="795520" d="5120">So it&#39;s definitely a good place to pass by 
those hours before dinner. But other than that,  </p>
<p t="800640" d="4160">is it worth going out of your way to go 
through here? I don&#39;t necessarily think so.</p>
<p t="804800" d="3360">Yeah, exactly. As you said, mi 
amor, it&#39;s only to have a drink  </p>
<p t="808160" d="3280">with someone of your friends or 
like hang around a little bit.</p>
<p t="811440" d="4400">And speaking of drinks with your friends, there&#39;s 
a cool bar on the other side of the city that is,  </p>
<p t="815840" d="2960">well, different than anything we&#39;d find in L.A.</p>
<p t="818800" d="9520">And one thing you need to know about us is that we 
personally are suckers for any kind of themed bar.</p>
<p t="828320" d="3360">We&#39;re at this place that is called 
Ferretería. That means “the hardware  </p>
<p t="831680" d="3680">store.” And we wanted to eat something 
over here, but we didn’t know that the  </p>
<p t="835360" d="5440">kitchen is closed certain hours. And 
we walked so far to get over here.</p>
<p t="840800" d="4880">But well, at least we&#39;re having a drink and we&#39;re 
admiring this place because it’s something else.  </p>
<p t="845680" d="6160">Along all the wall, there are certain things that 
you would buy in a place like this, you know.</p>
<p t="851840" d="4400">We’re not regretting it, but still, we need 
something to eat. I did the research. This  </p>
<p t="856240" d="5200">place is supposed to have very good food—but 
well, the kitchen is closed. What can we do?</p>
<p t="861440" d="4160">We decide to wander a bit when we come across a 
place that doesn’t look like much from outside,  </p>
<p t="865600" d="5920">but inside it’s packed with locals fresh out of 
work, eating some delicious and affordable tapas.</p>
<p t="871520" d="2960">This looks like our type of place. We 
really wanted to live the experience  </p>
<p t="874480" d="2560">of tapas and we found the right place to do it.</p>
<p t="877040" d="4400">This place is called Los Gatos. The menu is 
extensive, and I knew this was going to be a  </p>
<p t="881440" d="6240">good spot because when we sat down, they threw 
these delicious sausages in front of us—like,  </p>
<p t="887680" d="7920">smoked. So, so smoky and melt-in-your-mouth. 
They were so good. I want to figure out what  </p>
<p t="895600" d="4080">they were. And it was without asking. 
It was like “Welcome,” you know?</p>
<p t="899680" d="4240">It was amazing. So in front of us, we have 
several tapas, but we’re going to just keep  </p>
<p t="903920" d="4720">ordering more and more and more. These 
look delicious. I’m so glad we’re here.</p>
<p t="908640" d="3440">Yeah. No frills, no lines—just 
locals having tapas. And that’s  </p>
<p t="912080" d="3760">exactly what we wanted here in Madrid.</p>
<p t="915840" d="17440">Another day in Madrid. I’m excited for 
day two. I think it’s going to be a very  </p>
<p t="933280" d="3600">different day than it was yesterday. We 
have a lot of fun things to do today.</p>
<p t="936880" d="4400">Yeah. We’re starting off here in Plaza 
de España. What a gorgeous place.</p>
<p t="941280" d="6400">And what do you say we take a look through here 
before we head to our next stop—which is a museo.</p>
<p t="947680" d="2640">A museum. Which is a museo.</p>
<p t="950320" d="3440">A museum like you’ve never seen before.</p>
<p t="953760" d="1360">Sorry, what?</p>
<p t="955120" d="3200">A museum. A museum.</p>
<p t="958320" d="1200">Shut up.</p>
<p t="959520" d="5120">You know, we make these videos in English 
and Spanish. I get a little stuck sometimes.</p>
<p t="964640" d="1200">I love it. I love it.</p>
<p t="965840" d="6560">Anyway, let’s go to the mu—a muse.</p>
<p t="972400" d="3680">Okay, here’s a tip for you: 
don’t learn English from me.</p>
<p t="976080" d="5440">Okay, today we aren’t visiting a museum with 
ancient sculptures or dusty oil paintings.  </p>
<p t="981520" d="7200">This is a temple of taste—a monument to 
the noble pig. Welcome to Museo del Jamón.</p>
<p t="988720" d="4160">Inside, legs of ham dangle from 
the ceiling like holy relics,  </p>
<p t="992880" d="15440">and the energy is part deli, part fever dream.</p>
<p t="1009040" d="4240">And it has a very special place in my heart 
over here because every single day when we  </p>
<p t="1013280" d="4640">were in Madrid with my family—that is 
the best that I remember with them—we  </p>
<p t="1017920" d="4640">always wanted to have a breakfast over 
here. It was this juice, a sandwich,  </p>
<p t="1022560" d="3840">and a coffee. Every single day before 
we started exploring beautiful Madrid.</p>
<p t="1026400" d="4720">We&#39;re having this, and right now it&#39;s 
hard being over here without them,  </p>
<p t="1031120" d="5680">because I live now in the U.S. So it&#39;s difficult 
for me to see them, or it&#39;s difficult for me  </p>
<p t="1036800" d="6960">to have a trip with them—especially a great one 
